                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>“The way we’re accelerating science is unbelievable. In two or three years, things may look very different than they do today.&lt;/p>&lt;p>So we follow the science. Science means experiments and some experiments work, some don’t. But what happens is you learn. You learn why it didn’t work. You learn how to make it better.&lt;/p>&lt;p>We have to continue to invest in our vision, learn from failures and build on our successes. Because as long as patients are still suffering from disease, nothing’s good enough.”&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;em>– Ahmed Kotb, M.D., Vice President, U.S. Medical Affairs, Oncology, AbbVie&lt;/em>&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_2>
